Executive Profile
Scott M. Stuart  Co-Founder, Managing Partner, and Partner, Sageview Capital LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 18 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. Scott M. Stuart co-founded Sageview Capital LP in 2005 and has been its Managing Partner since 2005. Mr. Stuart serves as Head of Greenwich office and Partner at Sageview Capital. He served as a General Partner at KKR Associates since January 1995. Mr. Stuart served as a Partner of KKR & Co. L.P. from 1995 to 2005. He served as a General Partner at Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. (KKR) from January 1995 to January 1996, when he became a Member of the limited liability ... company, which is the General Partner of KKR. Mr. Stuart joined KKR as an Executive in 1986 and became a Partner in 1994. From 2000 to 2005, he was responsible for KKR's industry groups in the utilities and consumer products sectors. Previously, from 1981 to 1984, he was at Lehman Brothers Kuhn Loeb Inc., where he served in the Mergers and Acquisitions Department. He has been a Director of The Boyds Collection, Ltd. since April 1998. He served as Director of EverBank Financial Corp. from 2008 to June 9, 2017 and its Lead Independent Director until June 9, 2017. He serves as a Lead Independent Director of DMT Development Systems Group Inc. He has been a Director of Cadence Bancorp, LLC since 2010. Mr. Stuart serves as a Director of Cadence Bancorporation, United Capital Financial Advisers LLC, Newsquest PLC and Reflexis Systems, Inc. He is a Member of the Board at Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center. Mr. Stuart served as Director of Sealy Corporation at Sealy Mattress Company from April 2004 to April 22, 2009, Hexion Inc. since 1995, KKR Financial Holdings LLC from July 2004 to November 14, 2005, FCA US LLC from July 2009 to September 2011, Momentive Specialty Chemicals Inc. since 1995, Old Carco LLC since July 2009, World Color LLC since September 1992, The Dayton Power and Light Company since 2000 and DPL Inc. from 2000 to April 05, 2004. He served as a Director of KKR Financial Advisors LLC, KSL Recreation Group, Inc., and Sealy Mattress Corporation. He served as the Lead Independent Director of Duracell International, Inc. Mr. Stuart served on the Board of AEP Industries Inc. He served as a Trustee of The Boys' Club of New York. Mr. Stuart received an M.B.A. from Stanford University in 1986 and an A.B. in English from Dartmouth College in 1981.Read Full Background




